{"TopicId":177645,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Balancing a VTOL","CreatedByName":"Iguas","CreatedById":111055,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T10:48:14Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Iguas","CreatedById":111055,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T10:48:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey guys, i\u0027m currently designing a BIG \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E lander (600 T) that look\u00A0like a plane , so perfectly unsymmetrical and i\u0027d like to know if a mod can balance the fuel AROUND the center of mass, OR , if it doesn\u0027t exist, a mod that adjust the throttle to balance the craft ( i\u0027d prefer the first solution, as for now i only have 2 engines, and it would be difficult to adjust power for landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you ! have a good day \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow","CreatedById":65767,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T10:51:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not aware of a mod to balance fuel, though that\u0027s not to say that there isn\u0027t one.\u00A0 Whenever I have built a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E I try and make it so that the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E is the same empty as it is full which means the issue of an unbalanced craft doesn\u0027t arise, but I understand that this isn\u0027t always possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Iguas","CreatedById":111055,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T10:55:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223435896\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534589493\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002265767\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Scarecrow said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not aware of a mod to balance fuel, though that\u0027s not to say that there isn\u0027t one.\u00A0 Whenever I have built a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E I try and make it so that the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E is the same empty as it is full which means the issue of an unbalanced craft doesn\u0027t arise, but I understand that this isn\u0027t always possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYea, that was pretty much impossible, i\u0027ll try to shop you a picture,\u00A0 i mean, i COULD, but i\u0027d like to keep the \u0022plane\u0022 design (if you have any solution after i show picture, that\u0027s PERFECT ^^)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-18T10:56:34Z\u0022 title=\u002208/18/2018 10:56  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by iguas\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Iguas","CreatedById":111055,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T11:06:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223435896\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534589493\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002265767\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Scarecrow said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not aware of a mod to balance fuel, though that\u0027s not to say that there isn\u0027t one.\u00A0 Whenever I have built a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E I try and make it so that the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E is the same empty as it is full which means the issue of an unbalanced craft doesn\u0027t arise, but I understand that this isn\u0027t always possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022//imgur.com/gallery/zOKutY3\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAlbum gallery/zOKutY3 will appear when post is submitted\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\n(If you know how i can put picture directly on the forum, that would be cool too \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-18T11:08:37Z\u0022 title=\u002208/18/2018 11:08  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by iguas\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"katateochi","CreatedById":35181,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T11:36:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn invaluable mod is \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E build aid. It\u0027s not just for balancing \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E, infact that\u0027s the thing I use it for least. It helps you balance thrust and it adds markers for dry centre of mass and average centre of mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6810953681\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/166546-14-rcs-build-aid-continued-new-dependencies/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt doesn\u0027t do any auto engine adjusting and is only available in the editors, but it lets you get the initial balance setup nicely.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nLooking at your design, you\u0027ve got the engines positioned inline with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E, but that prob shifts forward as it burns fuel. My suggestion would be to add another \u003Cem\u003Esingle\u00A0\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E engine in the front, move the current ones aft slightly and then tune the thrust of the front engine.\u00A0 With \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E build aid you could then see what thrust value it would need to be when the craft is fully fuelled and when it\u0027s empty. Then during flight you can use the context menu for that single front engine and adjust it\u0027s thrust between those values. Depending on how much the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E moves, you might be able to get away with just balancing it for the average \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E and adding more \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E modules to account for the differences.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MisterKerman","CreatedById":189407,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T12:31:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds like you\u0027re F\u0027d in the A. I hope the rocket engine balancing idea works. I recently made a V-TOL\u00A0lander (The orientation or the engine in regards to it\u0027s docking ports I guess as all landers are... V-TOL...) but the fuel tanks are spread out evenly so balancing isn\u0027t an issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve always admired the concept of a V-TOL\u00A0plane and I\u0027ll most likely be in your shoes at some point soon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-18T12:33:09Z\u0022 title=\u002208/18/2018 12:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by MisterKerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"degenerate","CreatedById":139929,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T12:50:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThrottle Controlled Avionics is an amazing mod for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E ships.\u003Cbr\u003E\nhttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/97154-143-throttle-controlled-avionics/\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Laie","CreatedById":110461,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T13:02:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223435894\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534589294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111055\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022iguas\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, iguas said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey guys, i\u0027m currently designing a BIG \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E lander (600 T) that look\u00A0like a plane , so perfectly unsymmetrical and i\u0027d like to know if a mod can balance the fuel AROUND the center of mass,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo the best of my knowledge you have to build the vessel that way; \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E build aid helps with design by showing both full and empty \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, but it\u0027s still up to you to distribute the fuel load.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223435894\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534589294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111055\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022iguas\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, iguas said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmod that adjust the throttle to balance the craft\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMechjeb can basically do that, it\u0027s called \u0022differential throttle\u0022 and can be found under utilities. I guess it would suffice for your purposes. Throttle Controlled Avionics is a mod dedicated to balancing craft around many engines and will let you do a lot of crazy things, but getting to understand it and use it well is an undertaking in it\u0027s own right.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Iguas","CreatedById":111055,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T16:03:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110461-laie/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022110461\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110461-laie/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Laie\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/139929-degenerate/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022139929\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/139929-degenerate/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@degenerate\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/189407-misterkerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022189407\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/189407-misterkerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@MisterKerman\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/35181-katateochi/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002235181\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/35181-katateochi/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@katateochi\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/65767-scarecrow/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002265767\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/65767-scarecrow/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Scarecrow\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, i\u0027ll try all of this, thanks A LOT for your replies, this forum is god tier \u0026lt;3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mad Rocket Scientist","CreatedById":139256,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T20:35:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTAC fuel balancer will keep fuel balanced in VTOLs:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8482192261\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/139223-ksp-v145-tac-fuel-balancer-v220/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd TCA will keep unbalanced VTOLs level with throttle control:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3221832943\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/97154-143-throttle-controlled-avionics/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}